#=GF CC   Viral NSP8 (non structural protein 8) forms a hexadecameric
#=GF CC   supercomplex with NSP7 that adopts a hollow cylinder-like
#=GF CC   structure [1]. The dimensions of the central channel and
#=GF CC   positive electrostatic properties of the cylinder imply that it
#=GF CC   confers processivity on RNA-dependent RNA polymerase [1]. NSP7
#=GF CC   and NSP8 heterodimers play a role in the stabilisation of NSP12
#=GF CC   regions involved in RNA binding and are essential for a highly
#=GF CC   active NSP12 polymerase complex [2]. It has been demonstrated
#=GF CC   that NSP8 acts as an oligo(U)-templated polyadenylyltransferase
#=GF CC   but also has robust (mono/oligo) adenylate transferase
#=GF CC   activities [3]. NSP8 has N- and C-terminal D/ExD/E conserved
#=GF CC   motifs, being the N-terminal motif critical for RNA polymerase
#=GF CC   activity as these residues are part of the Mg2-binding active
#=GF CC   site [4].
